'''John Sterne[[Doctor of Divinity|DD]]''' was appointed [[Bishop of Bedford]] under the provisions of the [[Suffragan Bishops Act 1534]] in 1537 and held the post until his death in 1560<ref>[http://209.85.229.132/search?q=cache:va1-UyXLkFcJ:www.stalbans.anglican.org/content/download/318/2491/file/Section%2520A.pdf+John+Hodgkins+Bishop+of+Bedford&hl=en&ct=clnk&cd=2&gl=uk History of post]</ref>. Educated at [[Cambridge University]] <ref>[http://www.british-history.ac.uk/report.aspx?compid=37915 British History On-line]</ref>, from 1527 he was the [[Provincial (religion)| Provincial]] of the English Dominicans and [[Prior]] of [[Sudbury]]. In the course of a turbulent [[Episcopate]] he assisted in the [[Consecration]] of several [[Bishop]]s<ref>[http://www.newworldencyclopedia.org/entry/Matthew_Parker New World Encyclopaedia]</ref>.
